  <section style="background-color: white; padding: 20px; margin: 20px; border-left: 5px solid #C2185B;">
    <h2 style="color: #C2185B;">About Presley Chweneyagae</h2>
    <p>
      Presley Chweneyagae was a gifted South African actor best known for his lead role in the Oscar-winning film <em>Tsotsi</em>. Born in Mafikeng on October 19, 1984, Presley inspired many through his talent and commitment to social change.
    </p>
    <p>
      He starred in well-known shows such as <em>The River</em> as Thuso "Cobra" Mokoena and appeared in films like <em>Mandela: Long Walk to Freedom</em>. His performances were raw, powerful, and deeply meaningful.
    </p>
    <p>
      Beyond the screen, Presley was a community leader and founder of the Presley Chweneyagae Foundation, where he used theatre and performance to help youth in need. He will always be remembered not
